  "_comment": "Curated npm registry metadata fixtures for demo/package.json (time map + maintainers). Illustrative synthetic release histories designed to demonstrate the behavioral feature engine: lodash/chalk/uuid/debug/semver/commander/dotenv/yargs/picocolors/minimist/xml2js/axios/moment/node-ipc all have a mildly uneven but unremarkable release cadence and a healthy maintainer pool (normal; their severity, where non-Safe, comes from CVSS alone). colors has a single maintainer, an anomalously long dormancy, AND a disproportionate version jump (a strong behavioral anomaly, escalating its no-CVE Safe base to Low) - consistent with the real January 2022 colors/faker self-sabotage incident referenced in advisories.json. Feature computation only depends on the shape of this release history, not on the exact version string queried by the manifest scan.",

